description.text: this message file contains message for [name] package

msg.text: Secondary clock $$s has loads or driver cross to other module. Its skew cannot be guaranteed in the assembly flow.
Clock net $$s uses delayed mode. It will be routed using generic routing interconnect and might suffer from excessive delay or skew.

A remote spine is used for the normal clock net $$s, because the spine local to the driver is occupied by another net or is not able to route to all/most loads through the dedicated clock routing resource. This net might suffer from excessive delay or skew. You might need to check your preference file to see if more than one clock net is driven from the same block of four PIO cells that share a clock spine.
Unable to route net (PIO to PLL_$$s) with dedicated resource for net $$s.\n
Unable to route net (PIO to DCM_$$s) with dedicated resource for net $$s.\n
No primary Hspine is available for signal $$s.

The driver of primary clock net $$s is not placed on one of the sites dedicated for primary clocks. This primary clock will be routed to an H-spine through general routing resource and might suffer from excessive delay or skew.
There is no single load routed for secondary clock signal $$s.
Some loads of pclk net $$s have to be routed using general routing, because the DCS/DCC site is occupied by comp $$s.
No branch nodes have been found for the primary clock signal $$s. The signal will be routed with other routing resources.\n

The driver of edge clock net $$s is not placed on one of the dedicated sites or has no dedicated routing resource available. This edge clock will be routed through general routing resource and might suffer from excessive delay or skew.
There is no HSBX available for secondary clock signal $$s.

The driver of secondary clock net $$s is not placed on one of the PIO sites dedicated for secondary clocks. This secondary clock will be routed through general routing resource and might suffer from excessive delay or skew.

The driver of primary clock net $$s is not placed on one of the PIO sites dedicated for primary clocks. This primary clock will be routed to an H-spine through general routing resource and might suffer from excessive delay or skew.

The driver of bridge edge clock net $$s is not placed on one of the dedicated site for bridge clocks. This bridge edge clock will be routed to eclk through general routing resource and may suffer from excessive delay.
